text: When I was underage, in the US that is under 18, I desired to be sexual with females age 18 and much older, in fact I do not remember caring about age as a defining factor controlling my sexual drives.  As that young human being, I never thought of my desires as wrong or as if I were inviting rape, or that I was a pervert for wanting older females as well as my own age... furthermore I would never have been so cowardly and in denial of my responsibility for my sexual choices to have accused an older female of rape just for sharing with me what I desired of her in that sense.  Neither would I have allowed legal action taken against her on my behalf.  That is sick.  Our society is sick in this sense.  I think using legal adult age as a defining factor of whether a sexual encounter is rape or not is of course the general socialized and legalized norm for our brainwashed robotic sexually shamed and fear/denial based civilization, but in truth, much good sex and real love is exchanged between young people and adults of various ages, and I find it surprising so many sheeple have succumbed to this legal hatefest of denial of their sexual feelings and the truths of our real life sexual evolution regarding this particular dynamic where age is a man-made legal institution of shame-inducing control and power over ourselves as youths and adults.  Humans become sexually mature long before 18, that is a biological fact we have all lived through.  I never liked being controlled as a child or preteen or teen by adults and societal norms, such external expectations and bs hypocritical righteousness had nothing to do with my feelings and desires.
